We're so grateful for our friends at @sparkfinancialgroup who always provide us and our clients with up-to-date information on the mortgage rates and affordability to navigate any market.⁠
⁠
We took the average sale of Brantford-Brant-Norfolk, as often times we have clients who flow between these neighbouring counties, for a single detached home and compared the affordability to 1 year ago, in the over-inflated market.⁠
⁠
Right now consumers are nervous about interest rates, however, marry the house, not the rate.  Instead of locking in a higher fixed rate, why not discuss a variable rate which you can get as low as 5.55% right now with our advisors at Spark Financial? Bonus - if you ever have to break your mortgage, you aren't locked into a fixed term with high penalties! You simply pay the interest or 3 months! How fantastic is that!⁠
⁠
Another bonus is that when rates do go down, you can lock your rate in instead of waiting for your term to run out.  This is smart investing.⁠
⁠
If you take a look at this chart, you will notice the following:⁠
⁠
💫 1 year ago vs today you're paying HUNDREDS of THOUSANDS of dollars more on a home.  This means you're also not paying HUNDREDS of THOUSANDS of dollars off over time.
💫 1 year ago vs today, you're not paying COMPOUND INTEREST over time on that HUNDREDS of THOUSANDS! That is an outrageous amount of savings.⁠
💫 1 year ago vs today, your downpayment will be far less, as 20% of $965,000 vs 20% $690,000 = $55,000 less in down payment⁠
💫 1 year ago vs today with a variable rate, you are actually saving on your monthly payments.  The market was so incredibly inflated, even with low interest rates, you were still spending more.⁠
⁠
The proof is in the numbers.  The more you know 🌈⁠
⁠
For more information on affordability in this market, please contact me and my team.  We'd love to have you pre-approved with our friends at @sparkfinancialgroup who can guide you with affordability. ⁠
⁠

What a year.  I feel like I lived a decade in 365 days (and it's not even quite that yet)..⁠

Between opening two offices, growing my team, attending and speaking at 4 major conferences, collaborating and building strong relationships and everything in between...while running my own real estate business and being a mother/daughter/sister/friend/mentor/colleague 🥴⁠

Last night while on FaceTime with @_agent_jess_ we broke out into a fit of laughter while reminiscing about the year we had and the year we have ahead, we were reminded of how lucky we are to laugh, to smile, to live through it all with amazing people around us. I started this year out with big hopes and dreams and I am proud to say that after opening my letter from my future self a week early, the first time all year, that I wrote at the beginning of 2022, - I manifested the hell out of this year.⁠
⁠
So when I asked @meetingold to ask his next guest the surprise question, "was 2022 worth it?" - I find myself asking the same question, only to me. And yes.  2022 was absolutely frikkin' worth it.  Every last bit of it, topped with a layer of complete and utter fulfilment in every aspect of my life.  I just may need to lay down for a couple days to recover 😂⁠
⁠
Moving into 2023 with a grateful, joyful and appreciative heart.  And a lot of laughter, as always 🧡. Cheers to 2022.  I hope everyone enjoys the holidays with their family and loved ones.⁠

Did you know that the winter months are my absolutely FAVOURITE time to list properties?  The misconception is that the Spring is the best time. This holds true for Buyers as the vast majority of the inventory comes to market between March to June.

If you're a Seller, why would you want to be up against that much inventory?  That's silly 😏

In January and February:
💫 Inventory is low which equals higher demand
💫 New years resolutions hold true in real estate! Often buyers make new years resolutions to buy their first home, buy an investment, upgrade their home or change their location. 
💫 Longer closings (I mean, who wants to move in 5 feet of Canadian snow) allow for less stress on the Seller to find a suitable home AND inventory starts to really add up the closer to March!

This week I’m speaking at @thehousingcooperative about navigating uncertain times in real estate both as a solo agent and as a team.⁠
⁠
This brought me back to the root and foundation of my transformation as a person, an agent, a team leader and a business owner which was to start taking better care of me from the inside.⁠
⁠
We use the word “grind” as a positive adjective to describe a hard worker.  But it’s not.  Grind, to me, simply means grinding yourself into the ground.  I was living proof of this for many years.  I poured from an empty cup and often found it quite difficult to say no, even if it was at my own expense.⁠
⁠
At the conference that @kathleenblackinc held in November, I reflect on what has made me a top producer and an overall better person over the years, and that’s to take care of myself wholly; mind, body and soul.  The most fascinating part about this is once I started doing this, my business took off and I became a much calmer, less anxious and joyful person entirely. ⁠
⁠
And you know what? My sales have never been higher, my relationships have never been deeper and more meaningful and my overall lifestyle has become not just manageable, but fulfilling.⁠
⁠
Setting boundaries with others and yourself allows you to reach a potential thats rooted in values, optimism and enjoyment. ⁠
⁠
I’m excited for Thursday night as I start this talk as I relate this to overcoming any market with sharp focus and drive, along with major systems to focus on in today’s market.⁠

Have you ever heard of "The Shine Theory?" It's a concept I've vowed to live my life by each and every day; a commitment to the people I care deeply for to bring the most positive, authentic, version of myself with a great hope that this "shine" will be contagious so they too feel safe enough to show up and shine onto others.⁠
⁠
This theory is an investment, over the long term, in helping those feel safe and confident to be the best versions of themselves; to never let envy, rage, insecurity or hate come between themselves, others and their goal to be better people. “The Shine Theory” is recognizing that true confidence in oneself is infectious, and aids in cultivating a spirit of genuine happiness and excitement for those around you.  Its a theory that chooses acceptance and collaboration over rejection and competition. ⁠
⁠
You may have heard (or seen) me say "keep shining," on social media, or to my team, or to the people I love.  This phrase is intentional; it's recognizing the shining moments of others, and praising them for giving back to the world in the most positive way.  I feel uplifted when I see hard working, kind, passionate people shine onto others.  I find it motivating, captivating and above all else it helps me to raise the bar to shine myself.⁠
⁠
When I look at this picture I see a tight huddle of beautiful, authentic souls. They make me want to be better, do more and keep pushing through days that sometimes can feel bleak and overwhelming.⁠
⁠
The one thing I hope I give to them is the confidence to know that they are strong, intelligent, capable and marvellous human beings who can achieve anything they put their mind too.  They truly shine from the inside out and make the world a better place just by showing up ✨⁠

Our community is struggling.  So when there is struggle, it's imperative we step up in any way that we can.⁠
⁠
Right now, @thekatebroddickteam is working with @brantfordfoodbank to bring as many non-perishable food items to our community as possible from now until the Christmas season. ⁠
⁠
But if you dig a little deeper than this, if people are struggling to provide food to their families, how are they possibly affording warm winter wear during the upcoming winter season? The answer is - they're not. ⁠
⁠
I was driving to the office and realized we needed more than just our team to work this community event - so who do I call - none other than @realjoshuawall - our community ambassador extraordinaire - and team member of @thecrewrealestate.  I expected none other than the response I got - "Absolutely Kate, we're in - how do we help." ⁠
⁠
Since then, we've had @payitforwardrealtyinc & @andrewandkaterealestate join us to head an essential community winter wear drive.  Now more than ever we need to come together as a profession to keep our people "out of the cold" with warm winter wear this up-coming season.  We encourage all of our colleagues in real estate to join us on November 18th from 8-11pm at Mohawk Park to have a taste of what it's like to endure our Canadian winter evenings while collecting as many new or gently used winter items as possible to donate to those in need.⁠
⁠
Having 3 boys myself, it breaks my heart to think that someone's child isn't bundled up enough, or parents are going without to clothe their kids because times are tough.  This is when we need each other the most.⁠
⁠
If you're unable to come to Mohawk Park, we will be setting up collection bins @thekatebroddickteam office at our King George Road location during business hours.⁠
⁠
We are currently working toward finding organizations in need.  If you or anyone you know can help us with this event, please feel free to contact us at 519-729-TKBT.⁠

Hey @i.do.photography.ca remember in January of 2021 when we could only shoot inside and had to be creative "in the house." Those were dark days from March 2020 until the summer of 2022.  But, we had as much fun as we could with what we were given. ⁠
⁠
A Monday reminder that things can always be "worse."⁠
⁠
✨️ You may not love your job but you could be unemployed. ⁠
✨️ Your clients may be "frustrating" but you could have no clients at all.⁠
✨️You may not love your exterior but your health could be suffering.⁠
✨️ Money could be tight but you could be homeless. ⁠
✨️ Your children may drive you crazy but you could not be able to have any.⁠
⁠
Perspective is a major part of how your life will play out.  So perhaps instead of looking at the cup half empty, you could enjoy what you have in your cup and be grateful for what you have.⁠
⁠
Choose joy and gratitude.  You may find in doing so you become the richest person in the world 🥰⁠
